===Etymology===
From the Proto-Indo-European root ''*bhrāter-'' (''[[brother]]''). Cognates include the Old English ''[[broþor|brōðor]]'', and the English ''[[brother]]''; the Latin ''[[frater]]''; and the Russian ''[[брат]]'' (''brat'', meaning ''brother'').

===Noun===
'''brāti'''
# [[brother]] ''(biological brother)''
# [[comrade]] (as in an [[organisation]] or [[religious]] [[community]])

